 "awd_abstract_narration": "ABSTRACT                                  MCALISTER, Harold  AST-9414449    This grant provides partial support for the detailed design  and construction of a long-baseline, multiple-telescope  interferometric array operating at visible wavelengths.  The  CHARA Array will consist of five 1-m aperture telescopes in  a Y-shaped array contained within a 400 m diameter circle.  This configuration will provide high resolution  interferometry in the visible spectral region with a  limiting resolution of 0.2 milliarsec.  The facility will be  located on Mesa Negra, 130 km west of Albuquerque, New  Mexico.  The primary scientific programs will be directed at  the fundamental astrophysics of single and multiple stars  through interferometric analyses at visible wavelengths.  The Array will be applicable to problems in all areas of  contemporary astronomy, especially if it is later equipped  with adaptive optics and laser beacons.  The CHARA Array  will meet a critical goal of the Bachall Committee for  ground based interferometry for the 1990's and provide a  unique and powerful new astronomical facility for the  nation.  * * *",
